<text>Anchieta is a municipality in the Brazilian state of Espírito Santo. Its population was 29,779 in 2020 and its area is . Its average elevation is above sea level.

Formerly known as &quot;Reritiba&quot;, the city was renamed after the Jesuit Spanish missionary and saint José de Anchieta (1534-1597).

