<doc id="1119999" wikidata="Q734635" url="?curid=1119999" title="Nova Venécia">
<text>Nova Venécia is a Brazilian municipality in the state of Espírito Santo. Its population was 50,434 (2020) and its area is 1,448 km2. The seat of the municipality is at 65 meters above sea level.

Founded in 1888 with the name of Colônia de Santa Leocádia, it later became Colônia de Nova Venécia taking the new name from the Italian immigrants from the Veneto.

